# List Screen UI & Domain Patterns

When building or modifying list/table screens in this ERP, follow the patterns established in `lib/features/super_admin/presentation/screens/super_admin_schools_screen.dart`. Apply these consistently across the whole app.

## Super Admin module (`lib/features/super_admin/`)

All Super Admin screens must align with this rule file:

- **KPI / summary rows:** `MetricStatCard` + **`width >= 600`** → `Row` of `Expanded` tiles; **`width < 600`** → fixed height (~118) + horizontal `ListView` (~148px tiles). Same as Billing (`super_admin_billing_screen.dart`).
- **Table vs cards / two-column layouts:** use **`AppBreakpoints.tablet` (768)**, not ad-hoc `800` or raw `600`, unless a screen documents an exception.
- **Entity / admin list cards:** title row + **`HoverPopupMenu`** (`Icons.more_vert`); **`Divider`**; metadata + **chips** — avoid duplicate actions (no bottom **`IconButton`** row when the menu already covers actions).
- **Dense subscription / billing-style cards:** use **compact tappable tiles** (~60–70px). Card tap = opens detail sheet. No bottom `Manage`/`View` buttons. `PopupMenuButton(icon: Icon(Icons.more_vert, size: 18))` for mutating actions only. Two lines: (1) name + status pill, (2) metadata joined with ` · `. Add `clipBehavior: Clip.hardEdge` to `Card` + `InkWell` wrapping. Reference: `_buildMobileCard` in `super_admin_billing_screen.dart`.
- **Already reference implementations:** `super_admin_schools_screen.dart`, `super_admin_billing_screen.dart`, `super_admin_dashboard_screen.dart`.

## Layout Structure

Use **ListScreenLayout** (`lib/shared/widgets/list_screen_layout.dart`) when possible for consistent structure. Or build manually:

1. **RefreshIndicator** as root (pull-to-refresh)
2. **LayoutBuilder** > **Column** with:
   - Fixed header (title + actions)
   - Search + filters in a **Card** (centered)
   - **Expanded** table/list area (centered)

## Header Section

- Padding: `isNarrow ? 16 : 24` (breakpoint 600px)
- **Wrap** with `spacing: 12`, `runSpacing: 12`, `alignment: WrapAlignment.spaceBetween`
- Title: `Theme.of(context).textTheme.headlineSmall?.copyWith(fontWeight: FontWeight.bold)`
- Actions: `TextButton.icon` for secondary (e.g. Export), `FilledButton.icon` for primary (e.g. Add)

## Search + Filters

Reference: **Super Admin → Schools** (`super_admin_schools_screen.dart`, `_buildMobileSearchFilters`) — this is the **canonical mobile layout** (pill search + pill filter row + **Filters** button).

### Mobile filter strip (required look — do not improvise)

On **`MediaQuery.sizeOf(context).width < 600`** (or whenever the screen shows the **mobile** list layout), **do not** build ad-hoc `TextField` + `Wrap` unless you match this structure. **Reuse** `lib/shared/widgets/list_screen_mobile_toolbar.dart`:

| Widget | Role |
|--------|------|
| **`ListScreenMobileFilterStrip`** | Wraps the whole block; gives the **light tinted strip** behind search + filters (`surfaceContainerLowest` + padding). |
| **`ListScreenMobilePillSearchField`** | **Full-width** search: **pill** border (`AppRadius.brFull`), **white fill** (`surface`), **search icon** left, hint (e.g. “Search schools…”), optional clear. |
| **`ListScreenMobileFilterRow`** | **Second row:** **horizontal Row** with **equal-width** slots — each child wrapped in **`Expanded`** with **8px** gap. Put **2–3** primary filters here (e.g. Status “All”, Plan). |
| **`SearchableDropdownFormField`** | Each slot uses **`decoration: listScreenMobileFilterFieldDecoration(context)`** — **pill** outline, filled white, dense, chevron from the field. |
| **`ListScreenMobileMoreFiltersButton`** | **Third slot** (or last): **sliders icon** (`Icons.tune`), label **“Filters”**, **chevron** (`expand_more`), optional **active dot** when secondary filters apply; **`onPressed`** opens **`showModalBottomSheet`** with remaining filters (country/state/city, dates, etc.). |

**Order:** (1) header title + Add, (2) **strip** → pill search, (3) **filter row** → compact dropdowns + **Filters** button. **Never** hide the primary filters only inside the sheet unless the product spec says so.

### Component rules

- Use **`SearchableDropdownFormField`** / **`SearchableDropdownFormField.valueItems`** from `lib/widgets/common/searchable_dropdown_form_field.dart` for **every** filter that has more than a few static options (or needs search). Do **not** use raw **`DropdownButton`** for these.
- **Mobile / narrow popup:** when `MediaQuery.sizeOf(context).width < AppBreakpoints.formMaxWidth` (**600px**), the widget uses a **modal bottom sheet** for the option list automatically. Do not reimplement a different overlay unless there is a documented exception.
- **`useBottomSheet: true`:** set on a field when you must force the bottom sheet on **wide** layouts too (very long lists, overlay/z-index issues on web).
- **Closed field:** selected label must stay **single-line** with ellipsis (the widget uses a single-line painter on web); avoid layouts that let the value wrap into two lines.

### Layout — desktop / wide (filter **Card**)

- Wrap in **Center** > **Padding** > **Card** > **Padding(12)** > **Wrap**:
  - Search `~220px`, filters `~140px`, **Clear filters** text button; **not** the same as the mobile strip (no `ListScreenMobileFilterStrip` required on wide).

### Layout — mobile (narrow)

- Prefer **`ListScreenMobileFilterStrip`** + **`ListScreenMobilePillSearchField`** + **`ListScreenMobileFilterRow`** as in **Super Admin Schools** — **not** only a plain `Card` with `Column` unless you replicate the same pill styling and strip background.
- If a screen cannot import the shared widgets, **mirror** the same visuals: full-width pill search, second row of pill outlined fields + **Filters** (`Icons.tune` + label + chevron).

### “Filters” control

- When multiple secondary filters exist (location, date range, etc.), expose a single **Filters** control with a leading icon (e.g. **`Icons.tune`** or **`Icons.filter_list`**) + label **“Filters”** + chevron; **on tap** open **`showModalBottomSheet`** on mobile or a side panel / dialog on wide — do not stack six raw dropdowns on one row on phone.
- Keep **Clear filters** available: **`TextButton.icon`** with **`Icons.filter_alt_off`**, or inside the Filters sheet.

### Code review checklist (search + filters)

- [ ] **Mobile (`< 600px`):** uses **`ListScreenMobileFilterStrip`** + **`ListScreenMobilePillSearchField`** + **`ListScreenMobileFilterRow`** + **`listScreenMobileFilterFieldDecoration`** + **`ListScreenMobileMoreFiltersButton`** (or a documented deviation that matches the same screenshot).
- [ ] Filters use **`SearchableDropdownFormField`** (or documented exception).
- [ ] **Narrow width** uses bottom sheet for dropdown options (automatic via widget, or explicit **`useBottomSheet`**).
- [ ] **Filters** overflow / “more filters” is not a horizontal scroll of tiny broken dropdowns on mobile.
- [ ] No **DropdownButton** for multi-option searchable lists without justification.

## Pagination (Required for All Listing Tables)

Every list/table screen **must** implement pagination. Do not load unbounded data.

### Backend
- Accept `page` and `limit` query params. Return `pagination` object: `{ page, limit, total, total_pages }`.
- Cap `limit` at 100: `const parsedLimit = Math.min(parseInt(limit, 10) || 20, 100);`

### Frontend — Pagination (desktop) vs infinite scroll (mobile)

**Desktop / wide (`isWide` = `width >= AppBreakpoints.tablet`):** use **`ListPaginationBar`** (`lib/shared/widgets/list_pagination_bar.dart`) so the footer does not overflow on medium widths.

- The pagination row lives **inside the same Card** as the table (in the Card's `Column`), separated by a top border — **NOT** as a separate Card.
- Structure: `Card` > `Column` > [ `Expanded(ListTableView)`, `_buildPaginationRow()` ]
- **Wide**: left: showing text + Show/entries dropdown; right: `First | Previous | 1 2 3 … | Next | Last` (max 5 page numbers).
- Page size options: `[10, 15, 25, 50]` unless domain requires otherwise.

**Mobile / narrow (not `isWide`):** prefer **`MobileInfiniteScrollList`** (`lib/shared/widgets/mobile_infinite_scroll.dart`) instead of a bottom pagination bar:

- Load the first page (e.g. 15 items), then **append** the next page when the user scrolls near the bottom (~200px).
- Show a **footer** while loading more: skeleton placeholders + “Loading more…” + spinner (see implementation).
- Reuse the same API `page`/`limit` contract; the notifier or screen keeps `hasMore`, `isLoadingMore`, and `loadMore()` / `_load(append: true)`.
- Do **not** show `ListPaginationBar` on mobile for these screens — it wastes vertical space and stacks poorly.

## Table (Desktop/Wide)

- Use **ListTableView** inside **Card** > **Column** > **Expanded** inside **ConstrainedBox**
- Center the table with **Center** widget
- Show **ShimmerListLoadingWidget** (not CircularProgressIndicator) for initial loading
- Use `showSrNo: false` (no serial number column)

## Mobile list cards (canonical: `super_admin_schools_screen.dart`)

Use the same structure for **entity list** screens (schools, subscriptions, staff lists, etc.). Reference implementation: `_buildMobileCard` in `lib/features/super_admin/presentation/screens/super_admin_schools_screen.dart`. Platform **Schools** list mirrors this in `lib/features/schools/presentation/views/schools_screen.dart`.

### Structure

1. **Card** → **InkWell** (`borderRadius: AppRadius.brLg`) → **Padding** (`AppSpacing.paddingLg`) → **Column** (`crossAxisAlignment: stretch`).
2. **Top row:** **Expanded** title (16px semibold) + **`HoverPopupMenu`** (`Icons.more_vert`, 22px) for secondary actions. Do **not** duplicate the primary navigation action in the menu if the **card tap** already opens detail (e.g. omit “View” / “Manage”).
3. **Subtitle line (optional):** One line of metadata (`bodySmall` + `onSurfaceVariant`) — e.g. board · type, or code · state; avoid repeating the same field again below without reason.
4. **`Divider`** (`height: 1`, `outlineVariant` ~0.5 alpha, vertical padding ~10) separating header from body.
5. **Body row:** **Row** with **Expanded** left column and right column:
   - **Left:** Optional location row (`Icons.location_on_outlined`, 16px) + ellipsis; then **ID:** or equivalent identifier; then key metrics on one line (e.g. `Students: n · Faculty: m`) in muted text, `maxLines: 1`, ellipsis.
   - **Right:** **`Wrap`** of **`Chip`**s (plan + status) — `VisualDensity.compact`, `MaterialTapTargetSize.shrinkWrap`, plan chip with `side: BorderSide(color: outlineVariant)` and muted surface; status chip with semantic tint (`_statusColor`). Below chips, **Expiry:** or domain-specific date line, right-aligned.
6. **No** login URL / long URLs on the card unless the screen’s sole purpose is connection info.
7. **Do not** use a full **row of `IconButton`s** for View/Edit/Delete on mobile — use the **overflow menu**; **card tap** = primary drill-in (detail / manage).

### Breakpoints

- **`isWide`** for table vs cards: `MediaQuery.sizeOf(context).width >= AppBreakpoints.tablet` — **never** use `kIsWeb` alone to pick desktop layout on Flutter Web.

### Code review checklist (mobile list cards)

When reviewing or building a list screen, fail the review if any of these are missing without strong reason:

- [ ] Card tap performs the **primary** action; menu does not duplicate it.
- [ ] **⋮ menu** for destructive/secondary actions (edit, suspend, delete) instead of a bottom icon row on narrow layouts.
- [ ] **Plan + status** (or domain equivalents) shown as **chips** in the **lower-right** area, not only as plain text at the bottom.
- [ ] **Divider** between title block and detail block when the card has two visual zones.
- [ ] **Ellipsis** + `maxLines` on long labels; location line uses **icon + Expanded** text.
- [ ] Counts match **domain** definitions (e.g. `Student` / `Staff` tables vs user-role counts) and labels are clear (“Students”, “Faculty”).
- [ ] **Pagination:** desktop uses **`ListPaginationBar`** inside the table card; mobile uses **`MobileInfiniteScrollList`** (not a bottom page bar on phone).

### Older pattern (avoid for new work)

~~CircleAvatar + full-width chips under title + row of IconButtons~~ — migrate to the structure above when touching a screen.

## Metric / KPI stat cards (Billing & dashboard reference)

Use **`MetricStatCard`** from `lib/shared/widgets/metric_stat_card.dart` for **dashboard-style KPI strips** (MRR, ARR, totals, expiring counts) and any screen that shows the same visual language as **Super Admin → Billing** metrics.

### Visual contract (match Billing)

1. **White `Card`** with `RoundedRectangleBorder` + subtle **`outlineVariant`** border (`elevation: 0` when `compact`).
2. **Vertical stack (top → bottom):** tinted **icon container** (`padding: 8`, `borderRadius: AppRadius.brMd`, `color: accent.withValues(alpha: 0.15)`) → **bold value** (`titleLarge` / `titleMedium` when compact) → **label** (`bodySmall`, `onSurfaceVariant`, **`maxLines: 1`**, ellipsis). Optional **subtitle** line (e.g. “N active”) below label.
3. **Accent color** drives both icon tint and icon-box background (same hue, different alpha).

### Responsive layout

- **`MediaQuery.sizeOf(context).width >= 600`:** **`Row`** of **`Expanded`** `MetricStatCard`s (`compact: false`), separated by `SizedBox(width: 12)`.
- **`< 600`:** **`SizedBox`** fixed height (**118** if no subtitle, **~130** if optional subtitle) + **`ListView.separated`** horizontal scroll, each tile **`SizedBox(width: 148)`** + `MetricStatCard(compact: true)`.

### References

- Billing: `super_admin_billing_screen.dart` → `_buildBillingStats`.
- Dashboards using the same pattern: `super_admin_dashboard_screen.dart`, `group_admin_dashboard_screen.dart`, `school_admin_dashboard_screen.dart`.

### Code review checklist (metric cards)

- [ ] Uses **`MetricStatCard`** (or exact equivalent), not raw `Icon` + `Text` without the tinted box.
- [ ] Narrow layouts use **horizontal scroll**, not a 2×2 grid of tiny tiles.
- [ ] Value/label **do not wrap** unexpectedly; label uses **`maxLines: 1`**.

## Empty State

- **Card** or centered Column with:
  - Icon (entity-appropriate, size 64, `colorScheme.outline`)
  - Title text (e.g. "No schools found" or "No results for 'query'")
  - **TextButton** "Clear filters" when filters applied

## Error State

- **Card** with Icon(Icons.error_outline), error text, **FilledButton** "Retry"

## Dialogs

- Use **showAdaptiveModal** from `super_admin_dialogs.dart` (Dialog on web, BottomSheet on mobile)
- Use **kDialogMaxWidthLarge** (900) for large forms (Add School, School Detail)

### Mobile bottom sheet — drag handle + SafeArea

`showAdaptiveModal` wraps content in `SafeArea(top: false, ...)`. The `top: false` is intentional — if the dialog widget renders its own drag handle at the top (mobile only), `SafeArea` with `top: true` would push the handle down and waste space. Always keep `top: false` in `showAdaptiveModal`.

### TabBar inside mobile bottom sheet (4+ tabs)

When a dialog with a `TabBar` is shown as a bottom sheet on narrow screens, icon+text tabs overflow or truncate. Use this pattern:

```dart
final isMobile = MediaQuery.sizeOf(context).width < 600;

// Mobile: icon-only, evenly fills full width
if (isMobile)
  TabBar(
    controller: _tabController,
    isScrollable: false,   // evenly spans full width — no overflow
    tabs: const [
      Tooltip(message: 'Info',     child: Tab(icon: Icon(Icons.info_outline_rounded, size: 22))),
      Tooltip(message: 'Settings', child: Tab(icon: Icon(Icons.settings_rounded, size: 22))),
      // ... more tabs
    ],
  )
else
  // Desktop: icon + text, scrollable from left
  TabBar(
    controller: _tabController,
    isScrollable: true,
    tabAlignment: TabAlignment.start,
    tabs: const [
      Tab(icon: Icon(Icons.info_outline_rounded, size: 20), text: 'Info'),
      Tab(icon: Icon(Icons.settings_rounded, size: 20),     text: 'Settings'),
    ],
  )
```

**Rule:** Any dialog with ≥ 4 tabs must switch to icon-only on mobile (`< 600px`). Always add `Tooltip` for accessibility.

## Table row colors (AppThemeTokens)

`ListTableView` and `ReusableDataTable` apply alternating row colors from **`AppThemeTokens`**. These tokens are configured in the Super Admin Theme screen and must propagate to all tables at runtime — do not hardcode row colors.

| Token | Rows |
|---|---|
| `t?.tableRowEvenBg` | even rows (0, 2, 4 …) |
| `t?.tableRowOddBg` | odd rows (1, 3, 5 …) |
| `t?.tableHoverBg` | hovered / selected state |
| `t?.tableHeaderBg` | header row background |

```dart
// ✅ Always resolve from AppThemeTokens
final t = Theme.of(context).extension<AppThemeTokens>();
color: isSelected
    ? Theme.of(context).colorScheme.primary.withValues(alpha: 0.12)
    : (index.isEven ? t?.tableRowEvenBg : t?.tableRowOddBg),

// ❌ Never leave non-selected rows with null / transparent color
color: null,
```

Reference implementations:
- `lib/shared/widgets/list_table_view.dart` → `_buildDataRow`
- `lib/shared/widgets/reusable_data_table.dart` → `themedRows` generator

## Feedback — Toast notifications (AppToast)

Use **`AppToast`** (`lib/shared/widgets/app_toast.dart`) for success / error / warning / info toasts. It renders a **centered top-of-screen overlay** with a slide-in animation and an accent-coloured left strip — not a SnackBar at the bottom.

```dart
// ✅ Correct — centered overlay toast
AppToast.showSuccess(context, AppStrings.savedSuccess);
AppToast.showError(context, state.error!);
AppToast.showWarning(context, AppStrings.someWarning);
AppToast.showInfo(context, AppStrings.processingLabel);

// ❌ Forbidden for new screens — renders at bottom-left
ScaffoldMessenger.of(context).showSnackBar(SnackBar(content: Text('Saved!')));
```

**`AppFeedback`** remains the API for **confirmation dialogs, loading overlays, error banners, and status chips** — do not replace those with `AppToast`.

## Theme preview widgets (ConsumerWidget — not props)

Any widget that renders a **live theme preview** must watch the theme provider directly, not receive tokens as constructor parameters. `TabBarView`'s internal `PageView` skips rebuilds for off-screen tabs, so prop-passing silently breaks live updates.

```dart
// ✅ Correct — self-subscribing ConsumerWidget
class MyThemePreview extends ConsumerWidget {
  const MyThemePreview({super.key, required this.isLight});
  final bool isLight;

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
    final state = ref.watch(themeConfigProvider);
    final tokens = isLight ? state.lightTokens : state.darkTokens;
    // render preview using tokens
  }
}

// ❌ Wrong — tokens passed as prop; TabBarView won't rebuild off-screen tabs
class MyThemePreview extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyThemePreview({super.key, required this.tokens});
  final AppThemeTokens tokens;
  // ...
}
```

Always add a stable `ValueKey` to each `TabBarView` child: `key: const ValueKey('preview_table')`.

## Domain Terminology

- Schools (not "tenants" in UI)
- Status: Active, Trial, Suspended, Expiring
- Location: Country → State → City (use LocationData for dropdowns)
- Plans (subscription plans)
- Subdomain format: `{subdomain}.vidyron.in`

## Spacing & Breakpoints

- `isNarrow`: `MediaQuery.size.width < 600`
- **`isWide` (table vs cards):** `MediaQuery.sizeOf(context).width >= AppBreakpoints.tablet` (768). **Do not use `kIsWeb || …`** — on Flutter Web, `kIsWeb` is always true and would force the desktop table on narrow/mobile browser widths (bad horizontal scroll).
- Padding: 16 (narrow) / 24 (wide)

